love to be back in that ring

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:29.960
again and he couldn't.

00:12:29.960 --> 00:12:31.970
So I felt like I was
kind of doing it for him

00:12:31.970 --> 00:12:33.560
and he was living
through me, as well.

00:12:33.560 --> 00:12:35.600
So when he walked
in and everyone

00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:39.620
started chanting Ali and
then again when I came out.

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:42.350
I never really
focused on my dad when

00:12:42.350 --> 00:12:45.200
whether he was going to be there
or not because as a fighter,

00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:48.290
I like to just really be
focused on the mission at hand.

00:12:48.290 --> 00:12:50.059
I can't worry about
who's in the audience.

00:12:50.059 --> 00:12:50.600
None of that.

00:12:50.600 --> 00:12:53.330
And then after the fight,
I always looked for my dad

00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:56.780
and just kind of see that joy
and excitement in his eyes.

00:12:56.780 --> 00:12:59.630
- And when you look
at him, was it--

00:12:59.630 --> 00:13:03.650
again, I know, he was
gradually losing the abilities

00:13:03.650 --> 00:13:07.442
that obviously made him who
he was, but his personality--

00:13:07.442 --> 00:13:08.900
I mean, did you
see it in his eyes?

00:13:08.900 --> 00:13:10.520
- Oh yeah.

00:13:10.520 --> 00:13:13.670
- What would he do to
show you how much he

00:13:13.670 --> 00:13:15.590
