00:13:36.970 --> 00:13:38.514
and shorts in the ring with him.

00:13:38.514 --> 00:13:39.680
And I was like, dad, really?

00:13:39.680 --> 00:13:41.330
That's what you're
thinking about?

00:13:41.330 --> 00:13:44.420
But just being able to watch
me in the ring as a fighter

00:13:44.420 --> 00:13:46.970
and not seeing a woman, per
se, but seeing a fighter.

00:13:46.970 --> 00:13:50.310
And he knows that you
have to respect the game.

00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:53.450
He knows how hard it is to train
and to prepare and all of that,

00:13:53.450 --> 00:13:56.270
and it has nothing to do with
being a woman or being a man.

00:13:56.270 --> 00:13:58.610
So just for him to be able
to see past all of that

00:13:58.610 --> 00:14:00.500
and show me my respect,
and at the same time,

00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:02.630
be so surprised because he
wasn't there to see me train.

00:14:02.630 --> 00:14:04.140
He didn't know when
he was going to see.

00:14:04.140 --> 00:14:05.848
And then to be able
to see the way that I

00:14:05.848 --> 00:14:07.130
was able to dominate.

00:14:07.130 --> 00:14:10.520
And then, of course, it's
like, you're just like me.

00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:14.060
Now you want to take credit, OK.

00:14:14.060 --> 00:14:17.862
- So a few years after this,
through Billie Jean King

00:14:17.862 --> 00:14:19.820
and everyone at the
Women's Sports Foundation--

00:14:19.820 --> 00:14:22.820
some of the folks have
been around obviously here

00:14:22.820 --> 00:14:24.244
at the conference--

00:14:24.244 --> 00:14:25.910
the wonderful Women's
Sports Foundation,

00:14:25.910 --> 00:14:28.565
which does so much good work,
they basically kind of twist

00:14:28.565 --> 00:14:31.190
your arm and pretty soon you're
president of the Women's Sports

00:14:31.190 --> 00:14:32.780
Foundation.

00:14:32.780 --> 00:14:34.800
That's Billie Jean King for you.

00:14:34.800 --> 00:14:35.550
- She got me good.

00:14:35.550 --> 00:14:37.430
- Right, you say
hello, and now you're

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:39.410
president of the Women's
Sports Foundation.

00:14:39.410 --> 00:14:42.350
She knew what she was doing
because of your personality,

00:14:42.350 --> 00:14:45.050
because of everything that
you've just described for us.

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:50.210
So what did you take from your
personal experience and taking

00:14:50.210 --> 00:14:53.230
a dad-- in this case the
most famous dad in the world,

00:14:53.230 --> 00:14:53.990
one of them--

00:14:53.990 --> 00:14:55.970
and turning him
around and saying,

00:14:55.970 --> 00:14:58.190
hey, you can look at me as
an athlete, not as a girl.

00:14:58.190 --> 00:15:00.230
It's not just a girl
playing a sport.

00:15:00.230 --> 00:15:02.780
This is an athlete playing--
what did you then take,

00:15:02.780 --> 00:15:05.150
and how did that
help you as you then

00:15:05.150 --> 00:15:08.930
went to this global role of
being the face of women's

00:15:08.930 --> 00:15:10.352
sports for a couple of years?

00:15:10.352 --> 00:15:12.560
- This is one of those
questions I'm going to answer,

00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:15.143
and I get so deep I I'm going
to forget what the question was.

00:15:15.143 --> 00:15:17.300
- It's OK, that's why I'm here.

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:18.120
- Thank you.

00:15:18.120 --> 00:15:19.620
- Now if I forget,
we're in trouble.

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:20.510
- Right, right.

00:15:20.510 --> 00:15:25.640
The thing is that the way I
approach my career and life

00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:28.962
is that I never really worried
about what my dad thought,

00:15:28.962 --> 00:15:30.170
or what anybody else thought.

00:15:30.170 --> 00:15:32.150
I worried about what I
thought about myself.

00:15:32.150 --> 00:15:37.130
So for me, I had something
to prove to myself first,

00:15:37.130 --> 00:15:39.890
and I have really high
expectations of myself.

00:15:39.890 --> 00:15:44.540
So with my father,
I was just like--

00:15:44.540 --> 00:15:45.950
I've always been confident.

00:15:45.950 --> 00:15:47.730
I know I get that same
confidence from him

00:15:47.730 --> 00:15:49.650
because I had been training,
and I knew what I could do.

00:15:49.650 --> 00:15:51.740
I had already proved to
myself that I can do this,

00:15:51.740 --> 00:15:54.200
and I can be a champion, and
you're just going to sit back

00:15:54.200 --> 00:15:55.430
and you're going to watch.

00:15:55.430 --> 00:15:57.950
So for me, I was not
really concerned even

00:15:57.950 --> 00:16:00.361
with him going in because
it didn't hurt my feelings.

00:16:00.361 --> 00:16:02.360
I wasn't like-- I can't
believe my own father is

00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:05.300
not-- it's just like,
look, peace, see you later.

00:16:05.300 --> 00:16:08.297
I'm about to go do this,
and you can come along

00:16:08.297 --> 00:16:09.130
for the ride or not.

00:16:09.130 --> 00:16:11.900
So that was one thing
that took the burden off

00:16:11.900 --> 00:16:15.110
of myself to feel like
I had to please my dad

00:16:15.110 --> 00:16:16.340
or change his mind.

00:16:16.340 --> 00:16:18.560
I felt like that was
going to happen naturally,

00:16:18.560 --> 00:16:20.570
and that's the same
way that I've just

00:16:20.570 --> 00:16:23.750
approached the sport and life.

00:16:23.750 --> 00:16:25.670
It's too much to have
to worry about what

00:16:25.670 --> 00:16:27.200
everybody else is thinking.

00:16:27.200 --> 00:16:30.620
If I just stay focused on what
my goals are and be in the best

00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:33.770
that I can be because that
takes so much energy and focus

00:16:33.770 --> 00:16:38.300
and dedication to begin with,
then you can't do anything

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:40.670
but change your mind
at the end of the day

00:16:40.670 --> 00:16:44.420
because it is what it is if
you're honest with yourself.

00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:47.780
You know, so I think that
that's what changes--

00:16:47.780 --> 00:16:49.880
when people think women
can't do something,

00:16:49.880 --> 00:16:51.530
you see someone
do it, they think

00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:53.450
they can't because maybe
they've never seen it before,

00:16:53.450 --> 00:16:55.130
but as soon as you see it,
you learn something new,

00:16:55.130 --> 00:16:56.610
it changes that information.

00:16:56.610 --> 00:16:59.150
You're like, oh, so
I think right now

00:16:59.150 --> 00:17:01.790
my focus is just being
the best that I can be,

00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:03.990
and then inspiring
others along the way.

00:17:03.990 --> 00:17:07.040
But I try not to put that burden
on myself of I have to do this,

00:17:07.040 --> 00:17:08.690
and I have to do that, and I
have to please this person.

00:17:08.690 --> 00:17:10.190
I think that a lot
of times as women

00:17:10.190 --> 00:17:12.200
sometimes we do that
because we feel--

00:17:12.200 --> 00:17:14.770
and that's not to say that
I don't feel responsible

00:17:14.770 --> 00:17:17.020
and I don't make smart
choices along the way,

00:17:17.020 --> 00:17:21.339
because I do take being a
public person and a role model

00:17:21.339 --> 00:17:22.839
very seriously.

00:17:22.839 --> 00:17:25.359
There's opportunities
that come up that I have,

00:17:25.359 --> 00:17:27.730
and I'll turn them down
just because of the way

00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:31.739
it might come off, or
just because the message

00:17:31.739 --> 00:17:32.530
that it might send.

00:17:32.530 --> 00:17:34.590
Even though it might be
something I'm OK doing,

00:17:34.590 --> 00:17:36.430
I always have to think
about the long term effect.

00:17:36.430 --> 00:17:38.180
And I don't know if
anyone's ever noticed,

00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:41.677
but you don't really ever
see me showing too much,

00:17:41.677 --> 00:17:43.010
or having too much cleavage out.

00:17:43.010 --> 00:17:44.680
And a lot of people might
assume it's because I'm Muslim.

00:17:44.680 --> 00:17:45.430
I'm not.

00:17:45.430 --> 00:17:47.500
It's just that I don't
like for young girls

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:49.960
to feel like you
have to pose nude,

00:17:49.960 --> 00:17:52.240
or you have to do
certain things.

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:54.490
And at the same time, there
are some women that do it,

00:17:54.490 --> 00:17:55.823
and I don't judge them for that.

00:17:55.823 --> 00:17:58.240
Maybe they choose to do that,
but that's not who I am,

00:17:58.240 --> 00:18:01.270
and that's not the image
that I want to send.

00:18:01.270 --> 00:18:04.800
So here we are, and what
was the question again?

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:07.300
I have so much I want
to say, I was like--

00:18:07.300 --> 00:18:07.940
- No, no.

00:18:07.940 --> 00:18:09.100
Actually there's some
really great nuggets

00:18:09.100 --> 00:18:10.600
of things I'd love to pursue.

00:18:10.600 --> 00:18:12.430
But the Women's Sports
Foundation and being

00:18:12.430 --> 00:18:18.444
the president-- so
now you've got this--

00:18:18.444 --> 00:18:20.110
I was at the dinner
and you're speaking,

00:18:20.110 --> 00:18:22.350
and you're the face
of women's sports.

00:18:22.350 --> 00:18:24.520
You're no longer the
boxer, you've now

00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:27.640
graduated to this global role.

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:31.570
I guess the question was, your
experience and how then you

00:18:31.570 --> 00:18:34.780
were able to say, if the field
hockey people came to you

00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:35.500
or if someone--

00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:38.170
can maybe give us, if there
were moments-- maybe not--

00:18:38.170 --> 00:18:40.570
of where you gave advice,
or you were in meetings,

00:18:40.570 --> 00:18:43.350
or you could see sports
starting to emerge,

00:18:43.350 --> 00:18:45.100
which we see in the
Olympics all the time.

00:18:45.100 --> 00:18:47.530
Obviously we see in the
NCAA women's basketball.

00:18:47.530 --> 00:18:49.899
And now this is your
entire landscape

00:18:49.899 --> 00:18:51.940
that you are involved with
for a couple of years.

00:18:51.940 --> 00:18:53.648
- So when Billie Jean
first approached me

00:18:53.648 --> 00:18:57.810
about being the president of
the foundation, I was reluctant,

00:18:57.810 --> 00:19:00.190
and hesitant because
I was like wow,

00:19:00.190 --> 00:19:02.860
I didn't even grow
up playing sports.

00:19:02.860 --> 00:19:05.800
And there's so much there
as far as just organized

00:19:05.800 --> 00:19:07.960
sports and collegiate
sports and all these things.

00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:09.430
And just never played
it, and there's just

00:19:09.430 --> 00:19:11.346
this whole vocabulary
that goes along with it.

00:19:11.346 --> 00:19:14.020
I can't even really
have the conversation.

00:19:14.020 --> 00:19:15.940
So I was like, I don't
know if I'm the one.

00:19:15.940 --> 00:19:19.330
She's like, no you are the one
because you're that person.

00:19:19.330 --> 00:19:21.880
We want to get more
girls involved in sports,

00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:23.857
and you're someone who's
saying that I regret

00:19:23.857 --> 00:19:24.940
that I didn't play sports.

00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:27.370
And you see the importance
of it, and how it could have

00:19:27.370 --> 00:19:30.700
enriched my life, right?

00:19:30.700 --> 00:19:33.099
So I was like OK, I'll do it.

00:19:33.099 --> 00:19:34.640
And, of course, then
being around all

00:19:34.640 --> 00:19:37.030
these different women and
sitting in board meetings

00:19:37.030 --> 00:19:40.330
and listening to all the
issues is really overwhelming.

00:19:40.330 --> 00:19:45.320
But the fact that we're
in a time when we still

00:19:45.320 --> 00:19:48.410
see all the
disparities, then that

00:19:48.410 --> 00:19:51.680
means that we need strong
women that can stand up

00:19:51.680 --> 00:19:53.684
and can say something
that can inspire others.

00:19:53.684 --> 00:19:55.100
So it doesn't
really matter what I

00:19:55.100 --> 00:19:56.990
did and didn't do,
as long as I can have

00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:58.280
that conversation with people.

00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:02.044
So yes, now I'm an
advocate for sports,

00:20:02.044 --> 00:20:03.710
even though I didn't
play it growing up.

00:20:03.710 --> 00:20:05.668
I'm like, no, my kids
are going to play sports.

00:20:05.668 --> 00:20:09.102
I want the confidence building--

00:20:09.102 --> 00:20:11.060
what you learn about
yourself-- the discipline,

00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:12.110
working as a team.

00:20:12.110 --> 00:20:13.790
All these things
you learn in sports

00:20:13.790 --> 00:20:16.290
that you can apply to so many
different areas of your life.

00:20:16.290 --> 00:20:18.480
All of these successful
women that I've met

00:20:18.480 --> 00:20:21.590
said they believe that a
large part of their success

00:20:21.590 --> 00:20:23.210
is because they played sports.

00:20:23.210 --> 00:20:26.090
You learn so much about
yourself and about the world

00:20:26.090 --> 00:20:27.200
through sports.

00:20:27.200 --> 00:20:30.775
And as we've been
talking about--

00:20:30.775 --> 00:20:32.150
I know you guys
have been talking

00:20:32.150 --> 00:20:33.608
about the importance
of it, and how

00:20:33.608 --> 00:20:40.160
it kind of plays into society
in so many different ways

00:20:40.160 --> 00:20:41.212
and all of that.

00:20:41.212 --> 00:20:42.920
And it's true, and
I've seen that myself.

00:20:42.920 --> 00:20:47.420
So that's why I think
Billy asked me to be

00:20:47.420 --> 00:20:49.647
a president of the foundation.

00:20:49.647 --> 00:20:51.730
I will always be involved
with the Women's Sport--

00:20:51.730 --> 00:20:53.521
because once you get
in, you don't get out.

00:20:53.521 --> 00:20:56.786
Once you get in--

00:20:56.786 --> 00:20:58.160
- It's like the
Hotel California.

00:20:58.160 --> 00:21:00.750
- Right, right.

00:21:00.750 --> 00:21:03.020
- Here we are, the
45th anniversary

00:21:03.020 --> 00:21:04.910
