going to do like literally 30.

01:10:09.140 --> 01:10:10.360
Seconds can you guys do that?

01:10:10.360 --> 01:10:10.790
- Yes.

01:10:10.790 --> 01:10:10.990
- OK.

01:10:10.990 --> 01:10:11.090
You're up.

01:10:11.090 --> 01:10:12.309
- I'm Diane Rosenfeld.

01:10:12.309 --> 01:10:14.850
I teach at the law school and
run the Gender Violence Program

01:10:14.850 --> 01:10:16.100
there.

01:10:16.100 --> 01:10:17.360
And thank you for coming.

01:10:17.360 --> 01:10:20.430
And I wanted to bring
your dad into the room.

01:10:20.430 --> 01:10:24.065
I had the honor of
meeting him in '94.

01:10:24.065 --> 01:10:25.100
- Can you bring it up.

01:10:25.100 --> 01:10:26.750
- Yeah, absolutely
I'll bring it up--

01:10:26.750 --> 01:10:28.870
- Oh, after you say
what you're saying.

01:10:28.870 --> 01:10:31.910
And what really struck me about
him that is living through you

01:10:31.910 --> 01:10:34.940
is he had so much grace.

01:10:34.940 --> 01:10:36.500
And I see that in
you, and thank me

01:10:36.500 --> 01:10:39.643
for all your amazing
work and inspiration.

01:10:39.643 --> 01:10:42.008
- I appreciate that.

01:10:42.008 --> 01:10:45.510
And my very quick question
is I pay a lot of attention

01:10:45.510 --> 01:10:49.560
to gender equality in
sports and eliminating

01:10:49.560 --> 01:10:51.480
sexual harassment,
and sexual assault,

01:10:51.480 --> 01:10:53.400
and that angle of
Title IX, and I'm

01:10:53.400 --> 01:10:56.970
wondering what you think
about gender inclusive sports

01:10:56.970 --> 01:11:02.050
as a way to address the
sexism that exists in sports.

01:11:02.050 --> 01:11:05.140
That if kids grew up
playing with each other,

01:11:05.140 --> 01:11:07.150
and it wasn't like a boys
team and a girls team.

01:11:07.150 --> 01:11:08.486
- Your kids are now, right?

01:11:08.486 --> 01:11:09.610
- Yeah, I was going to say.

01:11:09.610 --> 01:11:13.440
- Your daughter's playing on
your son's Little League team.

01:11:13.440 --> 01:11:15.240
- So she plays on my
son's baseball team--

01:11:15.240 --> 01:11:16.240
- And we're going to
keep this to 30 seconds.

01:11:16.240 --> 01:11:17.280
- Yeah, I know.

01:11:17.280 --> 01:11:19.200
So I see on the field--

01:11:19.200 --> 01:11:20.130
my son plays soccer.

01:11:20.130 --> 01:11:22.290
I see girl's teams,
which is great.

01:11:22.290 --> 01:11:23.790
And I see some teams
where the girls

01:11:23.790 --> 01:11:26.123
are playing with the boys,
and I think that's wonderful.

01:11:26.123 --> 01:11:28.860
I think as long as it's
not a sport where power

01:11:28.860 --> 01:11:30.190
is going to come into play.

01:11:30.190 --> 01:11:31.230
Like a lot of times
people say, would you

01:11:31.230 --> 01:11:32.979
ever want to fight a
man, and I'm like no,

01:11:32.979 --> 01:11:33.960
because I want to win.

01:11:33.960 --> 01:11:36.469
I'm not going to fight a man--

01:11:36.469 --> 01:11:38.010
not that my skill
level isn't as high

01:11:38.010 --> 01:11:40.093
but the thing is I punch
harder than a lot of men,

01:11:40.093 --> 01:11:42.345
but they can take it,
and I start wearing down

01:11:42.345 --> 01:11:43.470
when they start hitting me.

01:11:43.470 --> 01:11:44.910
It's just the way that it is.

01:11:44.910 --> 01:11:45.810
There's nothing wrong with that.

01:11:45.810 --> 01:11:47.059
That's the way God created us.

01:11:47.059 --> 01:11:51.270
So if it's a sport where we
literally can be equal, then

01:11:51.270 --> 01:11:51.840
definitely.

01:11:51.840 --> 01:11:54.064
Like Billie Jean King
and her wonderful--

01:11:54.064 --> 01:11:54.980
- Beating Bobby Riggs.

01:11:54.980 --> 01:11:55.950
- Yeah, she beat him.

01:11:55.950 --> 01:11:56.820
And he was a man.

01:11:56.820 --> 01:12:00.210
So in some cases, I would say,
no, I don't want to see that.

01:12:00.210 --> 01:12:03.210
But for the most part, I think
it would be great, definitely.

01:12:03.210 --> 01:12:03.820
- OK, thanks.

01:12:03.820 --> 01:12:04.320
- Thank you.

